assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Linkers Corporation provides open support service for manufacturing companies in Japan. The company's solutions centered on business matching for various issues faced by manufacturing companies, such as searching for technical partners and developing users. It offers Linkers Sourcing, a service that searches for suitable technical partner that solve company's technical problems by utilizing network of industry coordinators, SMEs, and its database; Linkers Marketing that provides interviews through company-to-company matching; LFB, a matching system that supports business matching operations of introducing institutions; and Linkers Research that utilizing expert networks and IT to deliver technical information that matches the purpose. The company also provides TechMesse, a manufacturing technology platform that converts exhibitions into digital transformation and support lead acquisition for companies in various industries; and TechMesse Academy that holds an event to directly promote technology, products, and services to engineers of manufacturing companies, as well as provides one-stop support from content planning to after-sales follow-up for the realization of market development and cross-industry development. The company was founded in 2012 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
